        "timestamp": "2018-11-27 12:48:20.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(3 comments)\n\nBasically I'm fine with these changes. But could you describe (or point me to meaningful documentation) the disabled rules? I believe we should be as close to default rule-set as possible https://github.com/arturbosch/detekt/blob/master/detekt-cli/src/main/resources/default-detekt-config.yml",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "424f15c7e0494c5688a6744c76bd9e9fa7e75375",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3081,
          "name": "Jakub Dudycz",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jakub.dudycz@nokia.com",
          "username": "dudini1"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-11-27 13:06:44.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(2 comments)",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "744ddf3e680664d5c907529708afaf761d2dcea3",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3701,
          "name": "Filip Krzywka",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "filip.krzywka@nokia.com",
          "username": "fkrzywka"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-11-27 13:10:21.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n@jaszczyk\n\nUnfortunately the detekt-docs mostly points to outdated link. Rule documentation that I've used to know anyhting about rules is from detekt IntelliJ plugin (https://github.com/arturbosch/detekt-intellij-plugin).\n\nThe plugin presented me with following insight:\nParameterListWrapping - requires every indent in parameters (in functions, class constructor etc.) to be multiple of given in config and to always conform to kotlin-guideline, this is if parameters are in more than one line, they should all be on separate one\n```\nWRONG:\nWireFrameMessage(val payload: ByteData,\n                            val versionMajor: Short)\nCORRECT:\nWireFrameMessage(\n    val payload: ByteData,\n    val versionMajor: Short\n)\n```\nAs we don't really follow this rule, I disabled it.\n\nMatchingDeclarationName - https://arturbosch.github.io/detekt/naming.html#matchingdeclarationname\nWe did not follow kotlin guidline on this, could actually be reconsidered to apply it IMO.\n\nChainWrapping\nRequires to avoid lines starting with symbols when chaining expression like logical ones\n```\nWRONG:\nreturn true == true\n    && true == false\nCORRECT:\nreturn true == true &&\n      true == false\n```\nAs with prevoius examples we actually do not follow this convention in our code and I don't see reason to comply with it.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
